                    It is used to quantify how the rate constant of a reaction
                    changes with temperature, and to extract activation energy
                    and pre-exponential factors from kinetic data. It is widely
                    used in chemistry, materials science, catalysis, and
                    reliability engineering (e.g., accelerated aging tests for
                    electronics).
                  </div>
