                    before applying the Arrhenius equation.
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-md">
                  <button
                    type="button"
                    class="faq-question w-full text-left px-3 py-2 text-sm font-medium flex justify-between items-center"
                  >
                    <span
                      >Can I use this calculator for zero-order or second-order
                      reactions?</span
                    >
                    <span class="text-gray-400">+</span>
                  </button>
                  <div
                    class="faq-answer px-3 pb-3 text-sm text-gray-700 hidden"
                  >
                    Yes. The Arrhenius equation applies to the rate constant
                    regardless of reaction order. Just ensure that the units of
                    k and A are consistent with the reaction order (e.g.,
                    M⁻¹·s⁻¹ for second-order). The calculator treats k and A as
                    numerical values and does not enforce specific units.
                  </div>
