                    Curvature in an Arrhenius plot can indicate that the
                    activation energy changes with temperature, often due to a
                    change in mechanism, phase transitions, diffusion
                    limitations, or multiple parallel pathways. In such cases,
                    fitting a single straight line (single Ea) across the whole
                    range is not appropriate.
